Author: gretjia <gretjia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 22 11:07:42 2026 +0000

    experiment/phase-8 R1-R8: address dual-audit VETO + CHALLENGE items
    
    Phase 8 batch dual-audit (2026-04-22) returned:
      Gemini: CHALLENGE (3 items)
      Codex:  VETO (2 items) + CHALLENGE (3 items)
      Conservative verdict (feedback_dual_audit_conflict): **VETO**
    
    This commit addresses all 8 flagged items:
    
    R1 (Codex V-1 VETO): OracleReceipt was forgeable — pub fields + pub
    construction meant any in-process caller could mint a matching receipt.
    Fix: private fields; receipt binds (a) payload sha256, (b) parent-context
    sha256, (c) oracle-instance nonce. Bus requires register_oracle(nonce)
    before a receipt with that nonce is honoured. Lean4Oracle now has a
    private `nonce: u64` field (rand per-instance) + `nonce()` accessor.
    Context binding rejects cross-parent replay (step-mode tactic hijack).
    Tests: 2 new regression + updated constructor signatures (7 tests total).
    
    R2 (Codex Q6 VETO): oneshot used `TuringBus::new(...)` with `wal: None`
    → Halt event dropped when bus went out of scope. Paper C1 "Art. IV 100%"
    didn't hold for oneshot path. Fix: oneshot now opens
    `TuringBus::with_wal_path(wal/oneshot/<problem>_<ts>.wal.jsonl)` +
    `halt_and_settle(&[node_id])` so a durable `Halt{OmegaAccepted}` event
    survives on disk. Falls back to in-memory bus only on WAL open error
    (logged warn).
    
    R3 (Gemini+Codex CHALLENGE): has_bare_tactic_invocation false-positive on
    string literals + Unicode byte-boundary risk. Fix: new
    `strip_strings_and_comments()` helper (handles `"..."`, `-- ...`,
    `/- ... -/`); rewrote detection to use char-boundary iteration.
    Tests: 8 new (string / escape / line comment / block comment /
    mixed / Unicode identifier / Unicode-in-stripped-region / strip visible).
    
    R4 (Gemini CHALLENGE): `q_state` didn't restore across WAL replay —
    crash-resumed bus always reported Running. Fix: `with_wal_path` scans
    replayed events in reverse, restores q_state from last Halt event.
    Tests: 2 new (wal_replay_restores_q_state_halted / wal_replay_preserves
    _running_when_no_halt).
    
    R5 (Codex additional risk): snapshot surfaced `reputation` but prompt.rs
    didn't render it → agent can't actually see signal. Fix: added
    `own_reputation: u32` param to `build_agent_prompt`, rendered as
    "Reputation: N citations" line alongside Balance. Evaluator passes
    `snap.get_reputation(agent_id)`. All existing prompt tests updated.
    
    R6 (Codex CHALLENGE): halt_with_reason semantics of "live q_state" vs
    "durable ledger Halt event" needed clarification. Fix: expanded doc
    comment explaining the intentional split (live always latest; durable
    records first — halt_reason_distribution metric uses durable).
    
    R7 (Gemini CHALLENGE): Predicate trait (M-1 preservation) unused at
    Paper 1 scope. Fix: `#[allow(dead_code)]` with justification comment.
    
    R8 (Codex CHALLENGE): `#[serde(default)]` on reputation fields was
    logically correct but not regression-tested. Fix: 2 new tests
    deserialize pre-8.F JSON (missing reputation_by_author field) for both
    Tape and UniverseSnapshot; assert empty map default.
    
    Test count (post-R1-R8):
      turingosv4 lib:            119 pass
      minif2f_v4 lib:             24 pass (+8 R3 tests)
      snapshot_nonempty:           7 pass
      oracle_receipt_bus:          7 pass (2 new R1 VETO regression)
      rejection_threshold:         5 pass
      reputation:                  9 pass (+2 R8 serde tests)
      q_halt_state:                8 pass (+2 R4 WAL replay tests)
      wal_resume:                  2 pass
      reward_pull_conservation:    3/5 (pre-existing; Phase 8.Z task)
    
    Refs:
      handover/audits/EXT_GEMINI_PHASE_8_BATCH_2026-04-22.md
      handover/audits/EXT_CODEX_PHASE_8_BATCH_2026-04-22.md
      handover/ai-direct/EXT_AUDIT_PHASE_8_BATCH/brief.md
    
